<div class="modal fade keynote-details-modal" id="homeKeynoteGopakumarModal" tabindex="-1"
    aria-labelledby="homeKeynoteGopakumarTitle" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <div>
                    <span class="keynote-track">Power Electronics Keynote</span>
                    <h2 class="modal-title" id="homeKeynoteGopakumarTitle">Prof. K. Gopakumar</h2>
                    <p>Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore</p>
                </div>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="keynote-modal-profile">
                    <img src="/images/keynote/kgopa3.jpg" alt="Prof. K. Gopakumar" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
                        width="500" height="484">
                    <div>
                        <h3>Multilevel Inverters for Drives Application Using Open-End Winding Configuration for Motor with Extended Linear Sinusoidal Modulation Control</h3>
                        <p>Recently, numerous interesting multilevel topologies have been reported for motor drive applications. However, the most popular topology to date remains the neutral point clamped (NPC) three-level topology, especially for medium-voltage drive applications.</p>
                        <p>This shows that industry is still looking for a viable alternative with reduced power-circuit complexity and an extended linear sinusoidal modulation range. Conventional inverter-fed drive schemes will have substantial low-order harmonics in the extended linear modulation range, also known as the overmodulation range. This lecture will focus on recent work from Prof. Gopakumar's lab on cascaded basic inverter topologies with reduced DC-link voltages and sinusoidal PWM operation in the extended linear modulation range.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="modal fade keynote-details-modal" id="homeKeynoteSureshModal" tabindex="-1"
    aria-labelledby="homeKeynoteSureshTitle" aria-hidden="true">
